xsd:annotation.xsd:documentation: Builtin Simple types e.g. "xsd:date" have been used extensively to attempt to match the data types in the database tables. This typing may also provide hints to Oracle when it constructs sql types. Note that null values will not validate against "xsd:date" or "xsd:int," therefore elements typed this way must also be nillable (allowed to be null or empty).
It is possible to have a case with no MedicalRecords hence 0 minOccurs added, and MedicalRecords element nillable.
